title: Wall Street Breakfast November 29: Oil Slides Below $50
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description: Crude oil prices drop below $50 a barrel for the first time since October 2017; U.S. stock index futures are pulling back after a stellar session on Wednesday, and after a decade at the helm of Unilever, CEO Paul Polman has announced his retirement.
